title: Renaissance Medals - from S.H. Kress Collection (Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Phaidon | 1967 | Pdf | Eng | 307 pages | 49.3 MB

The medals catalogued and reproduced in the present volume were assembled by Gustave Dreyfus, an enthusiastic French collector of impeccable taste. Recognized as one of the finest private collections of Renaissance medals in existence, they were purchased by the Kress Foundation and given to the National Gallery of Art, Washington, D.C., in 1957
